Musikalische Ökosysteme in Wien — Vorstudie 2026

---

March 31

- language: markdown files and github commits in english. field names in german 
  (original austrian sources). data values in original german.
- corpus defined by venue, not genre
- OpenRefine: key features for this project are facets and clustering
- github repo created
- venue coordinates (lat/lon) saved in table — makes QGIS easier later

---

April 1–6

- sources found: Transparenzportal, data.gv.at, statistik.at via web search.
  MA7 Musikbeirat PDF via wien.gv.at. klingt.org, freemusicforum, esel.at
  from prior knowledge of the scene.
- time frame: 2022–2026. 2020–2021 out — pandemic distortion. 2026 upper limit
  includes IFG transparency data (nominative records from Sept 2025,
  §40k Transparenzdatenbankgesetz 2012).
- venue inclusion: at least one of: primary focus on experimental/improvised/
  electronic/contemporary music; documented publicly funded events; active role
  in the independent scene regardless of funding status.
- venues excluded: visual art only, dance only, commercial without scene connection.
- venue flags: * = secondary (not primarily music); ? = uncertain (academic/
  institutional context, decision pending).
- coordinates: verified manually via Google Maps and Google Plus Codes.
  unverified entries flagged.
- social media screenshots valid as event documentation source
- district calendars: weekly review source during data collection
- schalltaucherin.com: potential qualitative source, contact pending

Problems
- statistik.at: cultural data not filterable. discarded for now,
  maybe useful for aggregate context when writing.
- Transparenzportal: personal data redacted in PDFs. affects granularity
  of individual-level analysis.
- some venues host funded experimental events but aren't primarily
  known as experimental spaces — handled with inclusion criteria above.

