April 29

- git workflow: switched to terminal (git add / commit / push) from today.
  previous web interface uploads valid but no descriptive commit messages.
  no data lost.
- foerderung_ref: unified via sed batch replace —
  Stadt Wien Kultur / Staft Wien Kultur / MA7 Wien Kultur → MA7
  BMWKMS / BMKOES / BMKÖS → BMKöS
- MA7 is the canonical term (shorter, official, better for pandas groupby)
- WKO excluded from foerderung_ref — it's commercial sponsorship.
  distinction established:
  public funding: MA7, BMKöS, Bezirkskultur
  parafiscal: AKM, SKE, Musikfonds
  private: WKO, corporate — only first two go in foerderung_ref
- KÖR Wien: funding body for outdoor events, not a Verein —
  goes in foerderung_ref, not verein field
- radio broadcasts (Radio OE1 / ORF): removed from dataset —
  no spatial distribution, outside corpus definition
- theater productions: confirmed out (Theater am Werk -
  Da war ich nicht mehr da, 2 rows removed)
- recurring series: one real documented event per year, no generic
  placeholders. gaps are a documented limitation, covered by
  klingt_events_vienna.csv
- smallforms venue: Chateau Rouge (8. Bezirk), not Echoraum.
  wrong entries corrected.
- Der Blöde Dritte Mittwoch: Theater am Werk (1. Bezirk) through 2025,
  Echoraum (15. Bezirk) from April 2026 — venue shift after several years.
  flagged for interviews.
- Musikbeirat amounts: go in vereine table, not in foerderung_ref
- Vienna Club Commission: specific MA7 instrument for club/venue funding.
  Flucc funded via this programme.
- AIL: venue that hosts independent scene actors, not itself part of
  the MA7 funding ecosystem. Unsafe+Sounds used it in 2025.
  goes in venue field only.
- liccht - kulturverein für nischenmusik und populärkultur: confirmed
  via liccht.at/about. Musikbeirat 2026: 12.000€
- pre-IFG opacity treated as structural finding, not methodological gap:
  absence of centralized public funding data for 2022–2024 reflects
  how the ecosystem operates. who has access to funding information
  (organizations, MA7 officials, insiders) and who doesn't
  (researchers, public, new actors) is itself a finding about
  power structures. interview guide will address this directly.
- venue coordinates verified manually via Google Maps

